  <h2 id="accessibility">FULL Accessibility</h2>
  
  <p>
    All form components follow accessibility best practices:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>ARIA</strong>: <code class="inline-code">aria-invalid</code>, <code class="inline-code">aria-describedby</code>, <code class="inline-code">role="alert"</code> attributes</li>
    <li><strong>Linked labels</strong>: All fields have a label associated via <code class="inline-code">htmlFor</code> and <code class="inline-code">id</code></li>
    <li><strong>Required indicators</strong>: Red asterisk (*) for required fields</li>
    <li><strong>Error messages</strong>: Announced to screen readers with <code class="inline-code">role="alert"</code></li>
    <li><strong>Visible focus</strong>: Clear focus states on all interactive elements</li>
    <li><strong>Keyboard navigation</strong>: All components are keyboard accessible</li>
    <li><strong>Contrast</strong>: Meets WCAG AA ratios</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Complete accessible example</h3>

  <div class="example-section">
    <FormCard variant="initial" title="Accessible form" description="Example with all best practices">
      <FormGroup>
        <Label htmlFor="fullname-accessible" required>Full name</Label>
        <Input 
          id="fullname-accessible" 
          type="text"
          icon="mdi:account"
          placeholder="John Doe"
          required
          aria-label="Enter your full name"
        />
      </FormGroup>

      <FormGroup>
        <Label htmlFor="email-accessible" required>Email address</Label>
        <Input 
          id="email-accessible" 
          type="email"
          icon="mdi:email"
          placeholder="john.doe@example.com"
          required
          error="Invalid email format"
        />
      </FormGroup>

      <FormGroup>
        <Label htmlFor="country-accessible" required>Country</Label>
        <Select id="country-accessible" required>
          <option value="">Select your country</option>
          <option value="fr">France</option>
          <option value="be">Belgium</option>
          <option value="ca">Canada</option>
        </Select>
      </FormGroup>

      <Checkbox id="terms-accessible" name="terms" required>
        I accept the terms of use (required)
      </Checkbox>

      <Switch id="newsletter-accessible" name="newsletter">
        Receive the weekly newsletter
      </Switch>

      <ButtonComponent type="submit" variant="initial">Submit form</ButtonComponent>
    </FormCard>
  </div>

  <Code
